2732
02:26:50,415 --> 02:26:51,575
l do.

2733
02:26:55,378 --> 02:26:56,668
Dr. Hall.

2734
02:26:57,463 --> 02:26:59,553
l didn't know anyone was. . .

2735
02:27:00,675 --> 02:27:02,795
l'm sorry if l startled you.

2736
02:27:03,678 --> 02:27:05,298
l couldn't sleep.

2737
02:27:06,347 --> 02:27:09,767
And in trying
to resolve my dilemma,

2738
02:27:09,851 --> 02:27:12,771
l remembered something
l'd once read.

2739
02:27:12,854 --> 02:27:16,654
That a representative
owes the people
not only his industry,

2740
02:27:16,733 --> 02:27:19,233
but his judgment.

2741
02:27:19,318 --> 02:27:22,778
And he betrays them
if he sacrifices it
to their opinion.

2742
02:27:25,908 --> 02:27:28,288
That was written
by Edmund Burke,

2743
02:27:29,829 --> 02:27:32,329
a member of
the British Parliament.

2744
02:28:01,277 --> 02:28:03,197
Good night,
Mr. Adams.

2745
02:28:03,279 --> 02:28:04,609
Good night.

2746
02:28:15,708 --> 02:28:17,418
FRANKLlN:
It's never been done before.

2747
02:28:17,502 --> 02:28:20,092
No colony has ever broken
from the parent stem
in the history of the world.

2748
02:28:20,171 --> 02:28:22,841
DlCKlNSON:
lf you have grievances,
and l'm sure you have,

2749
02:28:22,924 --> 02:28:24,474
our present system
must provide

2750
02:28:24,550 --> 02:28:26,050
a gentler means
of redressing them

2751
02:28:26,135 --> 02:28:27,085
short of revoIution.

2752
02:28:27,178 --> 02:28:28,258
FRANKLlN: We've spawned
a new race here.

2753
02:28:28,346 --> 02:28:29,546
Rougher, simpler,

2754
02:28:29,639 --> 02:28:32,349
more violent,
more enterprising,
Iess refined.

2755
02:28:32,433 --> 02:28:35,893
THOMSON: "My quartermaster
has no food, no arms,
no ammunition,

2756
02:28:35,978 --> 02:28:38,438
"and my troops are in
a state of near mutiny."

2757
02:28:38,564 --> 02:28:40,824
DlCKlNSON: No army, no navy...
THOMSON: "l pray God
some reIief arrives

2758
02:28:40,900 --> 02:28:41,900
"before the armada,
but fear it wiII not."

2759
02:28:41,984 --> 02:28:43,074
DlCKlNSON: ...no arms,
no ammunition,

2760
02:28:43,152 --> 02:28:44,152
no treasury, no friends.

2761
02:28:44,237 --> 02:28:46,067
RUTLEDGE: And when
they hang you, Mr. Adams,

2762
02:28:46,155 --> 02:28:48,655
l do hope you'll
put in a good word
for the rest of us.

2763
02:28:48,741 --> 02:28:51,871
RODNEY: England closing in,
cutting off our air.

2764
02:28:51,953 --> 02:28:52,953
There's no time!

2765
02:28:53,037 --> 02:28:56,207
JEFFERSON: To place before
mankind the common sense
of the subject...

2766
02:28:56,290 --> 02:28:58,580
FRANKLlN: The issue here
is independence.

2767
02:28:58,668 --> 02:29:00,538
Perhaps you've lost
sight of that fact,
but I have not.

2768
02:29:00,628 --> 02:29:02,248
THOMSON: "We mutually pledge
to each other our Iives

2769
02:29:02,338 --> 02:29:05,338
"our fortunes
and our sacred honor."

2770
02:29:06,092 --> 02:29:09,092
ABlGAlL: Can you really know
so little about yourself?

2771
02:29:14,141 --> 02:29:15,481
Very well.

2772
02:29:17,395 --> 02:29:20,475
The Congress will now
vote on Virginia's
resolution on independence.

2773
02:29:20,565 --> 02:29:21,565
(DOOR OPENS)

2774
02:29:24,151 --> 02:29:25,361
(SlGHS)

2775
02:29:29,574 --> 02:29:30,824
Thank you for coming,
Caesar.

2776
02:29:31,784 --> 02:29:33,544
God bless you,
sir.

2777
02:29:39,041 --> 02:29:41,211
The secretary
will call the roll.

2778
02:29:41,294 --> 02:29:44,254
And l remind you, gentlemen,

2779
02:29:44,338 --> 02:29:46,508
that a single "nay" vote

2780
02:29:47,633 --> 02:29:49,553
will defeat the motion.

2781
02:29:50,845 --> 02:29:52,215
Mr. Thomson.

2782
02:29:57,393 --> 02:29:58,893
New Hampshire?

