02:30:00,521 --> 02:30:03,021
New Hampshire
says yea.
Massachusetts?

2785
02:30:03,107 --> 02:30:04,267
Massachusetts
says yea.

2786
02:30:04,358 --> 02:30:06,738
Massachusetts
says yea.
Rhode lsland?

2787
02:30:06,819 --> 02:30:08,149
Rhode lsland
says yea.

2788
02:30:08,237 --> 02:30:10,777
Rhode lsland
says yea.
Connecticut?

2789
02:30:10,865 --> 02:30:12,065
Connecticut
says yea.

2790
02:30:12,158 --> 02:30:14,948
Connecticut
says yea.
New York?

2791
02:30:15,036 --> 02:30:18,286
Mr. Secretary,
New York
abstains courteously.

2792
02:30:18,372 --> 02:30:19,502
New York abstains.

2793
02:30:19,582 --> 02:30:20,712
Courteously.

2794
02:30:22,126 --> 02:30:23,666
New Jersey?

2795
02:30:23,753 --> 02:30:25,053
New Jersey
says yea.

2796
02:30:25,129 --> 02:30:27,709
New Jersey
says yea.
Pennsylvania?

2797
02:30:29,717 --> 02:30:31,887
Mr. Secretary,
Pennsylvania
is not ready.

2798
02:30:31,969 --> 02:30:34,179
Please come back
to us later.

2799
02:30:34,263 --> 02:30:36,513
THOMSON:
Pennsylvania passes.
Delaware?

2800
02:30:36,599 --> 02:30:37,639
Just a moment.

2801
02:30:38,684 --> 02:30:41,944
Delaware,
by majority vote. . .

2802
02:30:42,521 --> 02:30:43,521
Aye.

2803
02:30:43,606 --> 02:30:45,186
. . .says yea.

2804
02:30:45,274 --> 02:30:48,234
Delaware says yea.
Maryland?

2805
02:30:48,319 --> 02:30:49,529
Maryland
says yea.

2806
02:30:49,612 --> 02:30:51,242
Maryland says yea.
Virginia?

2807
02:30:51,322 --> 02:30:52,362
Virginia
says yea.

2808
02:30:52,448 --> 02:30:54,528
Virginia says yea.
North Carolina?

2809
02:30:54,617 --> 02:30:57,367
North Carolina yields
to South Carolina.

2810
02:30:58,621 --> 02:30:59,621
South Carolina?

2811
02:31:00,623 --> 02:31:02,293
Well,
Mr. Adams?

2812
02:31:03,417 --> 02:31:04,707
Well,
Mr. Rutledge.

2813
02:31:07,797 --> 02:31:09,127
Mr. Adams,

2814
02:31:11,634 --> 02:31:15,604
you must believe
that l will do
what l promised to do.

2815
02:31:22,353 --> 02:31:23,943
What is it you want,
Rutledge?

2816
02:31:24,021 --> 02:31:27,651
Remove the offending passage
from your declaration.

2817
02:31:28,025 --> 02:31:30,145
lf we did that,
we would be guilty

2818
02:31:30,236 --> 02:31:33,146
of what we ourselves
are rebelling against.

2819
02:31:35,116 --> 02:31:37,326
Nevertheless remove it,

2820
02:31:38,077 --> 02:31:41,157
or South Carolina
will bury now and forever

2821
02:31:41,247 --> 02:31:43,327
your dream of independence.

2822
02:31:44,375 --> 02:31:47,835
John, l beg you,
consider what
you're doing.

2823
02:31:54,802 --> 02:31:56,432
Mark me, Franklin,

2824
02:31:57,555 --> 02:32:00,015
if we give in
on this issue,

2825
02:32:00,099 --> 02:32:02,599
posterity will
never forgive us.

2826
02:32:02,685 --> 02:32:04,765
That's probably true,
but we won't hear a thing.

2827
02:32:04,854 --> 02:32:06,944
We'll be long gone.

2828
02:32:07,023 --> 02:32:11,363
Besides, what will
posterity think we were?
Demigods?

2829
02:32:12,028 --> 02:32:13,608
We're men, no more,
no less,

2830
02:32:13,696 --> 02:32:16,566
trying to get
a nation started
against greater odds

2831
02:32:16,657 --> 02:32:19,527
than a more generous God
would have allowed.

2832
02:32:20,161 --> 02:32:23,411
First things first, John.
lndependence. America.

2833
02:32:23,497 --> 02:32:25,957
lf we don't secure that,

2834
02:32:26,042 --> 02:32:28,542
what difference
will the rest make?

2835
02:32:34,675 --> 02:32:36,675
Jefferson,
say something.

2836
02:32:39,138 --> 02:32:41,138
What else is there
to do?

2837
02:32:42,058 --> 02:32:44,808
Well, man,
you're the one
that wrote it.

2838
02:32:45,686 --> 02:32:48,806
l wrote all of it,
Mr. Adams.

2839
02:33:10,086 --> 02:33:11,286
There.

2840
02:33:11,378 --> 02:33:14,088
There it is, Rutledge.
You have your slavery.
Little good may it do you.

2841
02:33:14,173 --> 02:33:16,093
You now vote,
damn you !

2842
02:33:17,676 --> 02:33:21,466
Mr. President,
the fair colony
of South Carolina

2843
02:33:22,765 --> 02:33:24,345
says yea.

2844
02:33:24,433 --> 02:33:25,933
South Carolina
says yea.

2845
02:33:26,018 --> 02:33:29,558
North Carolina
says yea.

2846
02:33:31,107 --> 02:33:32,187
Georgia?

2847
02:33:32,274 --> 02:33:35,284
Georgia
says yea.

2848
02:33:36,612 --> 02:33:38,402
Pennsylvania, second call.

2849
02:33:40,449 --> 02:33:42,279
Mr. President,

2850
02:33:42,368 --> 02:33:45,538
Pennsylvania regrets
all of the inconvenience

2851
02:33:45,621 --> 02:33:50,671
that such distinguished
men as Adams,
Franklin and Jefferson

2852
02:33:50,751 --> 02:33:52,591
were put to
just now.

2853
02:33:52,670 --> 02:33:54,460
They might've kept
their document intact

2854
02:33:54,547 --> 02:33:57,127
for all the difference
it will make.

2855
02:33:57,216 --> 02:33:58,836
Mr. President,

2856
02:33:59,260 --> 02:34:00,640
Pennsylvania says. . .

2857
02:34:00,719 --> 02:34:01,799
Just a moment.

2858
02:34:03,472 --> 02:34:05,472
l ask the delegation
to be polled.

2859
02:34:06,225 --> 02:34:08,345
Dr. Franklin,
don't be absurd.

2860
02:34:08,811 --> 02:34:11,811
A poll, Mr. President.
lt's a proper request.

2861
02:34:12,064 --> 02:34:13,234
HANCOCK: Yes, it is.

2862
02:34:13,315 --> 02:34:15,605
Poll the delegation,
Mr. Thomson.

2863
02:34:15,693 --> 02:34:17,403
THOMSON:
Dr. Benjamin Franklin.

2864
02:34:17,486 --> 02:34:18,526
Yea.

2865
02:34:18,612 --> 02:34:20,572
THOMSON:
Mr. John Dickinson.

2866
02:34:20,656 --> 02:34:22,026
Nay.

2867
02:34:22,116 --> 02:34:23,736
THOMSON:
Mr. James Wilson.

2868
02:34:26,954 --> 02:34:28,414
Judge Wilson?

2869
02:34:31,584 --> 02:34:34,174
There it is,
Mr. Wilson. lt's all
up to you now.

2870
02:34:34,253 --> 02:34:35,923
The whole question
of American independence

2871
02:34:36,005 --> 02:34:38,585
rests squarely
on your shoulders.

2872
02:34:38,674 --> 02:34:42,224
An entirely new nation
ready to be born
or to die at birth,

2873
02:34:42,303 --> 02:34:44,013
all on
your say-so.

2874
02:34:45,139 --> 02:34:47,349
Which will it be,
Mr. Wilson?

2875
02:34:47,808 --> 02:34:51,348
Every mapmaker in
the world is waiting
for your decision.

2876
02:34:51,979 --> 02:34:55,109
Come now, James.
Nothing has changed.

2877
02:34:55,191 --> 02:34:57,941
We mustn't let
Dr. Franklin create
one of his confusions.

2878
02:34:58,027 --> 02:34:59,897
The question
is clear.

2879
02:35:00,404 --> 02:35:03,954
Most questions are clear
when someone else
has to decide them.

2880
02:35:04,033 --> 02:35:05,493
lt would be a pity
for a man

2881
02:35:05,576 --> 02:35:08,116
who's handed down
hundreds of wise decisions

2882
02:35:08,204 --> 02:35:10,044
from the bench

2883
02:35:10,122 --> 02:35:13,292
to be remembered only
for the one unwise decision

2884
02:35:13,375 --> 02:35:15,165
he made in Congress.

2885
02:35:16,629 --> 02:35:19,589
James, you're keeping
everybody waiting.

2886
02:35:19,673 --> 02:35:21,723
The secretary has
called for your vote.

2887
02:35:22,593 --> 02:35:23,803
Please.

2888
02:35:25,137 --> 02:35:28,717
Don't push me, John.
l know what you
want me to do.

2889
02:35:31,477 --> 02:35:34,267
But Mr. Adams is correct
about one thing.

2890
02:35:36,774 --> 02:35:39,534
l'm the one who'll
be remembered for it.

2891
02:35:39,818 --> 02:35:40,898
What do you mean?

2892
02:35:46,617 --> 02:35:48,827
l'm different from you, John.

2893
02:35:49,662 --> 02:35:52,412
l'm different from
most of the men here.

2894
02:35:53,374 --> 02:35:55,584
l don't want
to be remembered.

2895
02:35:56,835 --> 02:35:58,795
l just don't want the

2896
02:35:59,630 --> 02:36:01,170
responsibility.

2897
02:36:02,299 --> 02:36:04,799
Yes, well, whether you
want it or not, James,

2898
02:36:04,885 --> 02:36:07,135
there's no way
of avoiding it.

2899
02:36:07,221 --> 02:36:09,101
Not necessarily, John.

2900
02:36:09,765 --> 02:36:11,765
lf l go with them,

2901
02:36:11,850 --> 02:36:14,100
l'll just be one among dozens.

2902
02:36:15,938 --> 02:36:19,188
No one will ever remember
the name of James Wilson.

2903
02:36:20,567 --> 02:36:22,437
But if l vote with you,

2904
02:36:23,946 --> 02:36:27,276
l'll be the man
who prevented
American independence.

2905
02:36:30,119 --> 02:36:31,739
l'm sorry, John.

2906
02:36:33,163 --> 02:36:35,463
l just didn't
bargain for that.

2907
02:36:37,042 --> 02:36:40,462
And is that how new
nations are formed?

2908
02:36:41,880 --> 02:36:44,380
By a nonentity
trying to preserve

2909
02:36:44,466 --> 02:36:47,756
the anonymity he
so richly deserves?

2910
02:36:48,637 --> 02:36:50,007
Revolutions come
into this world

2911
02:36:50,097 --> 02:36:52,057
like bastard children,
Mr. Dickinson.

2912
02:36:52,141 --> 02:36:54,731
Half improvised
and half compromised.

2913
02:36:54,810 --> 02:36:57,230
Our side
has provided
the compromise.

2914
02:36:57,313 --> 02:36:59,983
Now Judge Wilson
is supplying
the rest.

2915
02:37:04,153 --> 02:37:05,323
James.

2916
02:37:06,864 --> 02:37:08,494
l'm sorry, John.

2917
02:37:09,533 --> 02:37:10,743
My vote

2918
02:37:11,952 --> 02:37:13,202


2919
02:37:13,996 --> 02:37:15,826
Mr. Secretary,
Pennsylvania says yea.

2920
02:37:18,667 --> 02:37:22,297
The count
being 1 2 to none

2921
02:37:24,423 --> 02:37:25,763
with one abstention,

2922
02:37:26,133 --> 02:37:28,343
the resolution on independence

2923
02:37:30,304 --> 02:37:31,684
is adopted.

2924
02:37:33,140 --> 02:37:39,150
lt's done.

2925
02:37:41,857 --> 02:37:43,227
Mr. Thomson,

2926
02:37:44,193 --> 02:37:45,783
is the declaration
ready to be signed?

2927
02:37:45,861 --> 02:37:47,491
lt is.

2928
02:37:47,571 --> 02:37:49,531
Then l suggest
we do so.

2929
02:37:51,367 --> 02:37:53,027
And the chair
further proposes,

2930
02:37:53,118 --> 02:37:55,828
for our
mutual security
and protection,

2931
02:37:57,748 --> 02:37:59,708
that no man
be allowed to sit
in this Congress

2932
02:37:59,792 --> 02:38:02,092
without attaching
his name to it.

2933
02:38:05,130 --> 02:38:08,010
l'm sorry, Mr. President.

2934
02:38:09,468 --> 02:38:13,758
l cannot,
in good conscience,
sign such a document.

2935
02:38:15,391 --> 02:38:19,641
l will never stop hoping
for our eventual
reconciliation with England.

2936
02:38:21,313 --> 02:38:23,483
But because,

2937
02:38:24,733 --> 02:38:26,233


2938
02:38:27,236 --> 02:38:30,736
l regard America no less
than does Mr. Adams,

2939
02:38:32,825 --> 02:38:36,695
l will join the army
and fight in her defense

2940
02:38:38,247 --> 02:38:41,327
even though l believe
that fight to be hopeless.

2941
02:38:47,005 --> 02:38:48,755
Goodbye, gentlemen.

2942
02:38:50,843 --> 02:38:53,013
JOHN: Gentlemen of
the Congress,

2943
02:38:53,095 --> 02:38:55,425
l say yea, John Dickinson.

2944
02:38:55,931 --> 02:38:57,811
(KNOCKlNG TABLES)

2945
02:39:03,981 --> 02:39:06,021
(lNDlSTlNCT CHATTERlNG)

2946
02:39:07,151 --> 02:39:08,481
Very well.

2947
02:39:09,445 --> 02:39:11,195
Are there any
objections to
the declaration

2948
02:39:11,280 --> 02:39:12,860
being approved
as it now stands?

2949
02:39:13,365 --> 02:39:14,485
l have one, Mr. Hancock.

2950
02:39:15,367 --> 02:39:16,907
You, Mr. Adams?

2951
02:39:17,453 --> 02:39:19,543
Yes. Uh, Mr. Jefferson,

2952
02:39:19,997 --> 02:39:24,127
it so happens that
the word is "unalienable,"

2953
02:39:24,209 --> 02:39:25,999
not "inalienable."

2954
02:39:27,713 --> 02:39:31,803
l'm sorry, Mr. Adams,
but "inalienable"
is correct.

2955
02:39:33,343 --> 02:39:36,513
l happen to be
a Harvard graduate,
Mr. Jefferson.

2956
02:39:36,597 --> 02:39:38,307
(LAUGHTER)

2957
02:39:39,641 --> 02:39:42,351
l attended William
and Mary, Mr. Adams.

2958
02:39:42,436 --> 02:39:43,686
(LAUGHTER)

2959
02:39:43,770 --> 02:39:45,020
Gentlemen,
please!

2960
02:39:45,105 --> 02:39:48,605
Mr. Jefferson,
will you yield to
Mr. Adams' request?

2961
02:39:50,944 --> 02:39:53,154
No, sir. l will not.

2962
02:39:59,870 --> 02:40:01,750
Oh, very well. l withdraw it.

2963
02:40:02,289 --> 02:40:03,999
Oh, good for you, John.

2964
02:40:04,082 --> 02:40:06,132
(LAUGHTER)

2965
02:40:08,670 --> 02:40:11,130
l'll speak to the printer
about it later on.

2966
02:40:12,633 --> 02:40:13,633
(SlGHS)

2967
02:40:13,717 --> 02:40:15,507
Very well, gentlemen.

2968
02:40:16,053 --> 02:40:19,893
We're about to brave the storm
in a skiff made of paper.

2969
02:40:21,099 --> 02:40:23,099
And how it shall end,

2970
02:40:23,185 --> 02:40:24,725
God only knows.

2971
02:40:26,730 --> 02:40:28,860
MAN: That's a pretty
large signature, Johnny.

2972
02:40:28,941 --> 02:40:32,281
So Fat George
in London can read it
without his glasses.

2973
02:40:32,361 --> 02:40:33,741
(LAUGHTER)

2974
02:40:34,655 --> 02:40:36,105
All right,
step right up,
gentlemen.

2975
02:40:36,198 --> 02:40:37,908
Don't miss
your chance
to commit treason.

2976
02:40:37,991 --> 02:40:39,241
ALL: Ooh.

2977
02:40:40,827 --> 02:40:44,867
Hancock is right.
This paper is our passport
